SvnoPsts-Agesilaus gets the throne but not without a struggle (1). He sets out to free Asia; he faithfully abides by a truce he makes with the Persians (2). Both in arms and in strategy he vanquishes the Persians (3). Summoned home because of the Corinthian war, he obeys and defeats his enemies at Coronea (4). Far from boasting of his victories, he laments the unhappy state of Greece (5). After the battle of Leuctra he saves Sparta from destruction (6). He helps his distressed country by all means in his power ; he lives very plainly (⁷). The Egyptians look with scorn upon his ill-shaped body and sim· plicity of dress. He dies on his way home from Egypt (8).
